data.title: The Midnight Ghost Train pulls in at JJ's Bohemia - Sept. 1
data.meta_description: The Midnight Ghost Train will be in concert Sunday, Sept. 1, at JJ's Bohemia, 231 E. M.L. King Blvd.
data.text:
The Midnight Ghost Train will be in concert Sunday, Sept. 1, at JJ's Bohemia, 231 E. M.L. King Blvd.

The heavy-metal rockers from Topeka, Kan., are touring in support of sophomore album "Buffalo."

Says singer/guitarist Steve Moss, "We wanted the sound of this record to be tangible. We wanted you to be able to close your eyes and feel and taste the sweat and blood that we give off onstage."

Others in the band are bassist David Kimmell and drummer Brandon Burghart.

The 21-and-older show starts at 10 p.m. with a $5 cover.

For more information, call 423-266-1400.
